    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-06-19T15:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-06-19T15:00:00-05:00" n="465"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d465">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">821.5151/285: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Colombia</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Dawson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Bogotá</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-06-19T15:00:00-05:00"
                            >June 19, 1935—3 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 4:50 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>60. The use of compensation marks by German competitor threatens to deprive
                    American bidders of a contract involving nearly 2 million pesos with the
                    Colombian Government for pipeline for Bogotá waterworks. Full report by air mail
                        today.<note n="18" xml:id="d465fn18">Despatch No. 83, June 19, 1935, not
                        printed. In despatch No. 194, August 16, 1935, the Minister in Colombia
                        reported that the Ministry of Public Works had accepted the bid of American
                        firms (621.6217/23).</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Dawson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
